Unofficial Translation by Insurance Regulator of Cambodia (IRC)

- A copy with the company seal of document on company bank account stating the minimum capital amount equivalent to 5,000,000 (five million) SDR;
- A copy with the company seal of document on company bank account proving the solvency of 50 (fifty) percent of the minimum capital;
- A copy with the company seal of document on business guarantee deposit in equivalent to 10 (ten) percent of the minimum capital;
- A copy with the company seal of patent or patent tax receipt;
- the contract of leasing or title deed which legalized by the local authority;
- A copy with the company seal of documents on the identification and qualifications of the person to be appointed as the chief executive officer such as passport or ID card, a resume on work experience and study with a degree or professional certificate;
- A copy with the company seal of documents on the identification and qualifications of the person to be appointed as the actuary such as passport or ID card, a resume on work experience and study with a degree or actuary certification;
- An original or a copy certified by notary of criminal record letter of the chief executive officer and the actuary.

After reviewing and evaluating the above required documents, the **IRC** has the right to issue a license or reject the application within 30 (thirty) days from the date of receiving sufficient documents.

**Article 8 ..**

Insurance company operating in the Kingdom of Cambodia shall request to renew the validity of general insurance company business license or life insurance company business license in order to obtain a new permanently valid license from the **IRC** before 30 (thirty) of business days of the expiration date of the license by attaching the required documents as below:
- the request letter for general insurance company business license or life insurance company business license renewal signed by chairman of the board of directors or the authorized director from the board;
- the company's declaration form completed and signed by chairman of the board of directors or the authorized director from the board in the form prescribed by the Director General of the Insurance Regulator of Cambodia;
- the receipt of administrative fee;
- the receipt of license fee;
- the original general insurance business license or life insurance business license;
- A copy with the company seal of the latest patent or patent tax receipt.

**Article 9 ..**

In case the insurance company operating in the Kingdom of Cambodia does not apply for renewing business licensing after the expiration date of the license, the company is considered to be operating the insurance business without the license.

**Section 2**
**The Issuance and Renewal of Certificates**
**of Local Insurance Company Branch**

**Article 10 ..**

Insurance company aims to establish a local insurance company branch shall apply for the certificate of local insurance company branch from the **IRC**.

